769
00:43:00,941 --> 00:43:06,480
Scott: I'm going to try to just watch the rest of the commentary on YouTube or something like that, because it's sort of annoying to have to play the whole game again.

770
00:43:06,620 --> 00:43:13,540
Scott: But anyway, the one thing in the commentary is like, you notice, they talk about it a lot, is there's this huge balancing act that goes on, right?

771
00:43:14,784 --> 00:43:18,819
Scott: They want the player to learn gradually, which they do a very good job at, right?

772
00:43:19,000 --> 00:43:23,160
Scott: A very good job of teaching you different concepts in the game one at a time.

773
00:43:23,240 --> 00:43:24,905
Scott: It's like, here's how to use a portal.

774
00:43:25,386 --> 00:43:26,389
Scott: Here's how to use a cube.

775
00:43:26,409 --> 00:43:27,693
Scott: Here's how to use a button.

776
00:43:27,974 --> 00:43:30,040
Scott: Here's how to use a cube and a button and a portal together.

777
00:43:30,200 --> 00:43:31,124
Scott: Here's how to do a jump.

778
00:43:31,164 --> 00:43:34,500
Scott: And they teach you the rules of the game very slowly and gradually.

779
00:43:34,781 --> 00:43:36,108
Scott: It's a good learning curve.

780
00:43:36,430 --> 00:43:37,133
Scott: Excellent job.

781
00:43:37,173 --> 00:43:38,380
Scott: They never messed that up, right?

782
00:43:39,121 --> 00:43:42,820
Scott: But what they do is they have so much playtesting, apparently, right?

783
00:43:42,920 --> 00:43:51,120
Scott: And they want to make the puzzles such that they get increasingly more difficult while introducing new elements.

784
00:43:51,602 --> 00:43:54,113
Scott: But they don't want to make them difficult in the wrong way.

785
00:43:54,133 --> 00:43:55,700
Scott: They're going for the Super Meat Boy, right?

